commit.message: cmake: add /utf-8 to MSVC compile flags, fix #757

BitHacks: remove assert(), fixes #756

This is basically a regression introduced into the MSVC code path in
https://github.com/zxing-cpp/zxing-cpp/commit/c661a3f22ee038394c1f9debff0a2d329be4ea05
but the problem was already present in a non-gcc-non-msvc code path.
dotnet: consistently use the `read.From()` name and bump version to 0.2.1
WriteBarcode: fix MSVC compiler warning
ci: add job to build experimental + c++20 configs
c-API: simplify ZX_GETTER macro
c-API: add missing bool properties in ZXingCTest
dotnet: add support for writing/creating barcodes based on experimental API
dotnet: introduce CheckError helper function
dotnet: fix bug in interpreting 1 byte c++ bools as 4 bytes c# bools
dotnet: rename Demo to DemoReader
cmake: use -Os also for RelWithDebInfo builds and add a few cpp files

cmake: add new experimental SupportedBarcodeFormats API

* reorganize building such that both reader (and new creator) APIs are
  always present but might fail on every call, depending on build mode
* new ZXingCpp.h as single point of entry for c++ API (similar to ZXingC.h)
* fix a few build issues with prior untested configurations

GTIN: strip a few kB of binary size

This sacrifices the "long" / non standard double county IDs like "US/CA".
Note that the linked sources of this data does not mention Canada either.
HRI: strip a few kB of binary size
python: only test symbologies supported by both old and new writer backend

WriteBarcode: fix color inversion from zint to BitMatrix

'1' == foreground == bit is set == black

DMDetector: tune recent improvement to fix introduced regression

This fixes #751.

ci: switch sanitize vm to ubuntu-20.04 to work around spurious seg-faults

See https://github.com/quantumlib/Stim/issues/717#issuecomment-2002623560.
test: fix overlooked unit test writer config
cmake: make the unit test target respect the READER/WRITER options

cmake: rename ZXING_HAS_... to ZXING_...

This brings the cmake option in line with the #define in Version.h

cmake: rename ZXING_BUILD_EXPERIMENTAL_API to ZXING_EXPERIMENTAL_API

This brings the cmake option and the pre-processor macro in line.

cmake: replace `BUILD_...` prefix of cmake options with `ZXING_...`

Care has been taken to keep the old names functional for a transition
period. A cmake warning is emitted in this case.
cmake: move CMAKE_WINDOWS_EXPORT_ALL_SYMBOLS from top-level to core
cmake: if (NOT CMAKE_CXX...) should have been if (NOT DEFINED CMAKE_CXX...)

python: change order of `text` and `format` arguments in create_barcode

This makes the API more consistent with the c++ one.
WriteBarcode: remove debug printf from release builds
ci: cleanup ci.yml
python: switch to libzint backend for standard setup.py builds (pip/wheel)
